00:10:25,666 --> 00:10:28,166
This is for a cause
that’s bigger than I am.

257
00:10:28,252 --> 00:10:30,002
If Gandhi could go
without eating

258
00:10:30,087 --> 00:10:33,797
for a whole three-hour movie,
I can do this.

259
00:10:33,883 --> 00:10:35,013
Besides,
I’m a woman.

260
00:10:35,092 --> 00:10:36,642
He’ll probably
go easy on me.

261
00:10:36,719 --> 00:10:37,849
Or kick the crap out of you.

262
00:10:37,928 --> 00:10:40,598
Watch your
language, moron.

263
00:10:40,681 --> 00:10:42,021
Hmm?

264
00:10:42,099 --> 00:10:44,389
(hard rock guitar riffs playing)

265
00:10:49,690 --> 00:10:51,480
(laughing)

266
00:10:51,567 --> 00:10:52,437
(grunts nervously)

267
00:10:54,278 --> 00:10:56,238
If I’m going to open a can
of whup-tushy,

268
00:10:56,322 --> 00:10:59,912
I’d better get in shape
with some rhythmic gymnastics.

269
00:10:59,992 --> 00:11:02,332
-(classical piano playing)
-Ah!

270
00:11:03,371 --> 00:11:05,581
Ah!

271
00:11:05,665 --> 00:11:06,915
Aha!

272
00:11:06,999 --> 00:11:08,919
♪ Ah-la! ♪

273
00:11:09,001 --> 00:11:09,921
♪ La-la-la-la-la! ♪

274
00:11:10,002 --> 00:11:11,462
Someone’s got
to stop her

275
00:11:11,545 --> 00:11:12,705
from going through
with this fight.

276
00:11:12,797 --> 00:11:15,927
This goes against every
feminist bone in my body,

277
00:11:16,008 --> 00:11:18,008
but Dad, can’t you control
your woman?

278
00:11:18,094 --> 00:11:19,804
How can I control her?

279
00:11:19,887 --> 00:11:21,427
I have nothing
to withhold!

280
00:11:21,514 --> 00:11:23,774
Oh, man, now she’s writing
cutesy things

281
00:11:23,849 --> 00:11:24,809
with the ribbon.

282
00:11:24,892 --> 00:11:26,772
(classical melody continues)

283
00:11:26,852 --> 00:11:28,982
(sighs)

284
00:11:30,189 --> 00:11:33,069
Ah-ah!

285
00:11:33,150 --> 00:11:34,740
Homer, this is bad.

286
00:11:34,819 --> 00:11:36,029
One unlucky punch

287
00:11:36,112 --> 00:11:37,952
and Marge could be
bedridden for life.

288
00:11:38,030 --> 00:11:40,780
Unable to move anything
but her left toe.

289
00:11:40,866 --> 00:11:41,986
Yeah.

290
00:11:43,828 --> 00:11:47,668
Oh, Marge, if only I knew
what these paintings meant.

291
00:11:47,748 --> 00:11:50,248
(sobbing)

292
00:11:50,334 --> 00:11:53,714
I know the woman I loved is
still in there somewhere,

293
00:11:53,796 --> 00:11:56,626
behind all this nonsense.

294
00:11:56,716 --> 00:11:59,046
We’ve gotta get Marge some
professional training.

295
00:11:59,135 --> 00:12:02,045
Carl, do you know heavyweight
champ Drederick Tatum?

296
00:12:02,138 --> 00:12:03,678
What? You think just
’cause I’m black

297
00:12:03,764 --> 00:12:04,774
I know all other
black people?

298
00:12:04,849 --> 00:12:06,269
Well, I, uh, uh...

299
00:12:06,350 --> 00:12:08,520
Actually, Drederick and I
are very good friends.

300
00:12:08,602 --> 00:12:09,942
We met through
Dr. Hibbert

301
00:12:10,020 --> 00:12:12,110
at a party at Bleeding
Gums Murphy’s house.

302
00:12:12,189 --> 00:12:14,609
Well, Marge, you have definitely
come to the right crib.

303
00:12:14,692 --> 00:12:15,902
I’m always happy

304
00:12:15,985 --> 00:12:17,605
to impart
my pugilistic prowess

305
00:12:17,695 --> 00:12:19,275
to a punching parvenu.

306
00:12:19,363 --> 00:12:22,323
Now, the first lesson will
be to work the tattoos.

307
00:12:23,576 --> 00:12:25,036
Flaming skull.
Obama.

308
00:12:25,119 --> 00:12:27,119
Scooby-Doo. Scooby-Doo.
Scooby-Doo.

309
00:12:27,204 --> 00:12:28,914
Now, work
"The Lord’s Prayer."

310
00:12:28,998 --> 00:12:30,708
I’m gonna order
some lion food.

311
00:12:30,791 --> 00:12:31,881
Hello? Yeah,
how you doin’?

312
00:12:31,959 --> 00:12:34,709
I’d like to order
two gazelles, an impala,

313
00:12:34,795 --> 00:12:36,375
and throw in a couple
of wildebeests.

314
00:12:36,464 --> 00:12:39,054
Oh, and a two-liter bottle
of diet cherry cola.

315
00:12:39,133 --> 00:12:40,553
You just have
one-liter bottles?

316
00:12:40,634 --> 00:12:41,514
Okay, cancel
the whole order.

317
00:12:43,345 --> 00:12:47,055
The second element of mixed
martial arts is jujitsu,

318
00:12:47,141 --> 00:12:49,231
in which we use an
opponent’s strength

319
00:12:49,310 --> 00:12:50,480
against himself.

320
00:12:50,561 --> 00:12:53,271
But I sneak some of my
strength in there, too.

321
00:12:53,355 --> 00:12:54,265
(chuckles)

322
00:12:54,356 --> 00:12:57,106
Now, attack me
with great anger!

323
00:12:57,193 --> 00:12:58,283
(karate yell)

324
00:12:58,360 --> 00:12:59,450
Surprising move!

325
00:12:59,528 --> 00:13:01,108
(groans)

326
00:13:01,197 --> 00:13:02,737
Next: Homer, <i>hajime!</i>

327
00:13:02,823 --> 00:13:04,873
(karate yell)

328
00:13:04,950 --> 00:13:06,290
Mmm? Hmm?

329
00:13:06,368 --> 00:13:08,288
Now, we stick foot in mouth,

330
00:13:08,370 --> 00:13:10,000
tie arms like pretzel,

331
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:13,170
and pop discs in spine
like bubble wrap.

332
00:13:13,250 --> 00:13:15,210
(popping)

333
00:13:15,294 --> 00:13:16,674
(chuckles)

334
00:13:16,754 --> 00:13:17,714
Is he okay?

335
00:13:17,797 --> 00:13:19,757
Oh, he feels no pain.

336
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:20,970
(muffled screams)

337
00:13:21,050 --> 00:13:23,640
Sorry, my English
is not so good.

338
00:13:23,719 --> 00:13:25,639
I mean, he feels
only pain.

339
00:13:25,721 --> 00:13:26,511
(muffled screech)

340
00:13:26,597 --> 00:13:28,017
(classical music plays)

341
00:13:28,098 --> 00:13:29,768
Back when I wrestled at Yale,

342
00:13:29,850 --> 00:13:31,690
I was in the lightest
weight category--

343
00:13:31,769 --> 00:13:32,689
"ether weight."

344
00:13:32,770 --> 00:13:34,770
Now, get ready to
face the wrath

345
00:13:34,855 --> 00:13:36,185
of the "New Haven Nuisance!"

346
00:13:37,733 --> 00:13:40,193
<i>CHORUS:</i>
<i>♪ Boola Boola, Boola Boola ♪</i>

347
00:13:40,277 --> 00:13:41,857
<i>♪ Boola Boola... ♪</i>

348
00:13:41,946 --> 00:13:43,236
(grunting)

349
00:13:43,322 --> 00:13:45,202
(grunts, gasps)

350
00:13:45,282 --> 00:13:47,082
(grunting)

351
00:13:47,159 --> 00:13:48,369
Side-mount!

352
00:13:48,452 --> 00:13:49,412
Takedown! Advantage!

353
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:50,745
Reversal! Reversal!

354
00:13:50,830 --> 00:13:52,460
Clinch! Clinch, I say!

355
00:13:52,540 --> 00:13:54,380
(sighing):
Listen,

356
00:13:54,458 --> 00:13:56,838
I’m late
for a PTA meeting.

357
00:13:56,919 --> 00:13:58,299
In order to save money,

358
00:13:58,379 --> 00:14:00,629
the following presidents
will no longer be taught:

359
00:14:00,714 --> 00:14:03,844
Buchanan, Fillmore,
Pierce, Bush, Bush--

360
00:14:03,926 --> 00:14:05,926
could you please stop that?

361
00:14:06,011 --> 00:14:07,391
Saratoga slam!

362
00:14:07,471 --> 00:14:08,601
Aristotle’s dilemma!

363
00:14:08,681 --> 00:14:09,971
Knickerbocker
knucklebreaker!

364
00:14:10,057 --> 00:14:11,177
And so on.

365
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:12,517
(snoring)

366
00:14:12,601 --> 00:14:14,811
Marge, I bet
we got ten minutes

367
00:14:14,895 --> 00:14:16,895
till the kids wake up.

368
00:14:16,981 --> 00:14:18,611
(both moaning)

369
00:14:18,691 --> 00:14:21,361
-Marge! Marge! Marge!
-Huh?

370
00:14:21,443 --> 00:14:22,193
(gasp, scream)

371
00:14:22,278 --> 00:14:24,988
Tomorrow night your bedroom
will be the septagon.

372
00:14:25,072 --> 00:14:27,372
Your sleeping pill
will be my punches.

373
00:14:27,449 --> 00:14:29,199
By the way, what’s that book
you’re reading?

374
00:14:29,285 --> 00:14:30,865
<i>Eat, Pray, Love.</i>

375
00:14:30,953 --> 00:14:33,463
More like "Beat, Slay, Shove!"

376
00:14:33,539 --> 00:14:35,579
The fireworks begin tomorrow!

377
00:14:35,666 --> 00:14:37,376
(fireworks whistling, popping)

378
00:14:37,459 --> 00:14:39,339
I said tomorrow!

379
00:14:39,420 --> 00:14:40,420
No can do.

380
00:14:40,504 --> 00:14:41,634
We’re out of fireworks.

381
00:14:41,714 --> 00:14:43,304
Why’d you shoot ’em off now?

382
00:14:43,382 --> 00:14:45,552
I have trouble concentrating.

383
00:14:45,634 --> 00:14:47,554
I should be on antidepressants.

384
00:14:47,636 --> 00:14:48,796
Ugh. Where was I?

385
00:14:48,888 --> 00:14:49,968
"Beat, Slay, Shove."

386
00:14:50,055 --> 00:14:52,015
Right-- "Beat, Slay, Shove!"

387
00:14:52,099 --> 00:14:54,519
The fireworks start tomorrow!

388
00:14:54,602 --> 00:14:56,192
(fireworks whistling, popping)

389
00:14:56,270 --> 00:14:58,770
I found some more,
but that was it!

390
00:14:58,856 --> 00:14:59,856
Mmm.

391
00:15:02,776 --> 00:15:05,816
A lot of people think
bullies are born awesome,

392
00:15:05,905 --> 00:15:08,445
but the fact is,
we have to train.

393
00:15:08,532 --> 00:15:11,992
You don’t get garlic knots like
these unless you work the bag.

394
00:15:12,077 --> 00:15:14,497
(whistling)

395
00:15:14,580 --> 00:15:17,120
-(grunts)
-(groans)

396
00:15:17,207 --> 00:15:19,537
-(giggles)
-Is there someone in there?

397
00:15:19,627 --> 00:15:21,127
It’s my own fault.

398
00:15:21,211 --> 00:15:23,841
I looked them in the eye when
I gave them my lunch money.

399
00:15:23,923 --> 00:15:26,053
Someone should tell
your principal!

400
00:15:26,133 --> 00:15:27,763
I’m well aware
of the situation.

401
00:15:27,843 --> 00:15:31,723
(electric organ playing
melodramatic melody)

402
00:15:35,851 --> 00:15:37,191
Mom,

403
00:15:37,269 --> 00:15:38,649
I came here to tell you

404
00:15:38,729 --> 00:15:40,649
it’s not too late
to back out.

405
00:15:40,731 --> 00:15:42,481
I can’t back out,

406
00:15:42,566 --> 00:15:44,226
because if I fight him
tomorrow,

407
00:15:44,318 --> 00:15:47,448
it’ll be a less violent world
for you kids in the future.

408
00:15:47,529 --> 00:15:49,449
There must be
a better way.

409
00:15:49,531 --> 00:15:51,621
HOMER:
There certainly is!

410
00:15:51,700 --> 00:15:54,410
Marge Simpson reporting
for duty!

411
00:15:54,495 --> 00:15:56,535
(Marge-like murmuring)

412
00:15:56,622 --> 00:15:59,082
Dad, I keep telling you,
that won’t work.

413
00:15:59,166 --> 00:16:00,326
Let’s go, Marge.

414
00:16:00,417 --> 00:16:02,537
My class reunion starts
in an hour.

415
00:16:02,628 --> 00:16:04,628
Uh, Moe, I have
a confession to make.

416
00:16:04,713 --> 00:16:06,473
I’m just Homer
dressed as Marge.

417
00:16:06,548 --> 00:16:09,088
Yeah, but last year I took
Barney dressed as Marge.

418
00:16:09,176 --> 00:16:10,586
Think how much better
they’ll think you look.

419
00:16:10,678 --> 00:16:11,848
Mmm?

420
00:16:11,929 --> 00:16:13,059
Well, you’d better
not leave me

421
00:16:13,138 --> 00:16:14,718
and talk to your
old friends all night.

422
00:16:14,807 --> 00:16:17,267
Keep talkin’ like that
and I’ll leave you
here right now!

423
00:16:17,351 --> 00:16:18,811
(fanfare playing)

424
00:16:18,894 --> 00:16:21,984
Krusty, I’m honored
you invited me tonight.

425
00:16:22,064 --> 00:16:24,364
Yeah, I thought
a noisy public place

426
00:16:24,441 --> 00:16:25,821
would be the best spot
to tell you

427
00:16:25,901 --> 00:16:27,031
that I’ve been
dating your wife.

428
00:16:27,111 --> 00:16:28,321
(gasps)
What?!

429
00:16:28,404 --> 00:16:30,494
Also, could you tell her
I’m dumping her?

430
00:16:30,572 --> 00:16:32,492
After 11 years,
the thrill is gone.

431
00:16:32,574 --> 00:16:34,284
I... I... uh...

432
00:16:34,368 --> 00:16:37,328
Marge, I tried my best to
talk you out of this.

433
00:16:37,413 --> 00:16:40,173
But since you’re going through
with it, I beg you,

434
00:16:40,249 --> 00:16:43,669
just stay out of his way
and don’t get hurt.

435
00:16:43,752 --> 00:16:45,842
And, Mom, if you punch
him in the junk,

436
00:16:45,921 --> 00:16:47,721
you’ll get no disrespect
from me.

437
00:16:47,798 --> 00:16:49,588
Hey, Bart, did you know
that’s a haiku?

438
00:16:49,675 --> 00:16:51,545
BART:
Huh?

439
00:16:51,635 --> 00:16:52,755
(grunts)

440
00:16:52,845 --> 00:16:55,135
-(bell clanging in arena)
-(groans)

441
00:16:55,222 --> 00:16:56,602
(audience chattering)

442
00:16:56,682 --> 00:16:59,352
Time to square off in the ring--

443
00:16:59,435 --> 00:17:01,595
that is, The Septagon!

444
00:17:01,687 --> 00:17:04,017
In this corner,
weighing in at...

445
00:17:04,106 --> 00:17:05,686
Nobody needs to know that!

446
00:17:05,774 --> 00:17:06,534
Skip ahead!

447
00:17:06,608 --> 00:17:08,488
Stands the "Mom
I’d Like To Fight"--

448
00:17:08,569 --> 00:17:10,529
Marge Simpson!

449
00:17:10,612 --> 00:17:13,452
(cheering, applause,
whistling)

450
00:17:13,532 --> 00:17:17,542
And four obtuse angles over,
weighing in at 115 pounds,

451
00:17:17,619 --> 00:17:20,999
Chett Englebrecht!

452
00:17:21,081 --> 00:17:22,921
CROWD (chanting):
Chett! Chett! Chett!

453
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:26,590
Chett! Chett! Chett!
Chett! Chett! Chett!

454
00:17:26,670 --> 00:17:28,920
And, now... let’s begin

455
00:17:29,006 --> 00:17:31,506
to rumba!

456
00:17:31,592 --> 00:17:33,432
We’ve been ready for hours!

457
00:17:33,510 --> 00:17:37,470
I had car <i>trouble!</i>

458
00:17:37,556 --> 00:17:38,306
(clangs)

459
00:17:38,390 --> 00:17:40,730
(cheering)

460
00:17:40,809 --> 00:17:41,889
Don’t worry, Marge.

461
00:17:41,977 --> 00:17:42,807
Don’t want to hurt you.

462
00:17:42,895 --> 00:17:45,015
-(sighing) I knew it!
-Pow!

463
00:17:45,105 --> 00:17:47,435
(groans)

464
00:17:47,524 --> 00:17:50,694
That’s the first time I ever hit
a woman I didn’t love. Wow.

465
00:17:53,906 --> 00:17:55,696
(groaning)
Nine... aah!

466
00:17:55,783 --> 00:17:57,793
Come on! Come on!
Get back on your feet!

467
00:17:57,868 --> 00:17:58,908
I believe in you!

468
00:17:58,994 --> 00:18:00,454
I’m doin’ it, Moe!

469
00:18:00,537 --> 00:18:01,537
Not you.

470
00:18:01,622 --> 00:18:02,372
Oh, thank God.

471
00:18:02,456 --> 00:18:03,826
The pressure’s off.

472
00:18:03,916 --> 00:18:04,876
(panting)

473
00:18:04,958 --> 00:18:06,038
I’ll save you,
Marge!

474
00:18:06,126 --> 00:18:07,956
(groans)

475
00:18:08,045 --> 00:18:09,415
(gagging)

476
00:18:09,505 --> 00:18:10,545
(grunting)

477
00:18:10,631 --> 00:18:12,051
Hit my Mom, will ya?

478
00:18:12,132 --> 00:18:14,302
Well, I’m gonna knock you out
and moon your corpse.

479
00:18:14,384 --> 00:18:15,894
